Title: 2ZR-FXE (INTAKE / EXHAUST): EXHAUST MANIFOLD: REMOVAL; 2019 MY Prius [12/2018 - 08/2019]

REMOVAL

CAUTION / NOTICE / HINT

The necessary procedures (adjustment, calibration, initialization or registration) that must be performed after parts are removed and installed, or replaced during exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst) removal/installation are shown below.

Necessary Procedures After Parts Removed/Installed/Replaced

Replaced Part or Performed Procedure

Necessary Procedure

Effect/Inoperative Function when Necessary Procedure not Performed

Link

  • Replacement of air fuel ratio sensor
  • Gas leak from exhaust system is repaired

Inspection After Repair

  • Poor idle, etc.
  • Engine start function, etc.

CAUTION:

  • To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust manifold or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.
  • To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

6. REMOVE FRONT FLOOR COVER LH

(a) Remove the 2 bolts and 3 clips and disengage the 6 clamps to remove the front floor cover LH from the vehicle body.

Bolt

Clip

7. REMOVE FRONT FLOOR COVER RH

HINT:

Perform the same procedure as for the front floor cover LH.

8. REMOVE FRONT CENTER FLOOR BRACE

(a) for Type A:

(1) Remove the 12 bolts and 3 front center floor braces from the vehicle body.

*A

Type A

*B

Type B

(b) for Type B:

(1) Remove the 8 bolts and 2 front center floor braces from the vehicle body.

9. REMOVE FRONT EXHAUST PIPE ASSEMBLY (TWC: Rear Catalyst)

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

(a) w/ Exhaust Heat Recirculation System:

(1) Slide the 2 clips and disconnect the outlet heater water hose B and outlet heater water hose C from the inlet water pipe and No. 2 outlet water pipe.

*1

Outlet Heater Water Hose B

*2

Outlet Heater Water Hose C

*a

No. 2 Outlet Water Pipe

*b

Inlet Water Pipe

(b) Disconnect the heated oxygen sensor connector.

(c) Disengage the wire harness clamp.

(d) Remove the 4 bolts and 4 compression springs and disconnect the front exhaust pipe assembly (TWC: Rear Catalyst) from the exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst) and tail exhaust pipe assembly.

*A

w/ Exhaust Heat Recirculation System

*B

w/o Exhaust Heat Recirculation System

(e) Remove the front exhaust pipe assembly (TWC: Rear Catalyst) from the 2 exhaust pipe supports.

(f) Remove the 2 exhaust pipe gaskets from the exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst) and front exhaust pipe assembly (TWC: Rear Catalyst).

10. REMOVE WIRING HARNESS CLAMP BRACKET

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

(a) Disengage the clamp and remove the bolt and wiring harness clamp bracket from the cylinder head sub-assembly.

11. REMOVE NO. 1 EXHAUST MANIFOLD HEAT INSULATOR

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

(a) Remove the 6 bolts and No. 1 exhaust manifold heat insulator from the exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst).

12. REMOVE MANIFOLD STAY

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

(a) Remove the 3 bolts and manifold stay from the exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst) and cylinder block sub-assembly.

13. REMOVE EXHAUST MANIFOLD (TWC: Front Catalyst)

CAUTION:

To prevent burns, do not touch the engine, exhaust pipe or other high temperature components while the engine is hot.

(a) w/ Exhaust Heat Recirculation System:

(1) Remove the nut and disconnect the water pipe and hose sub-assembly A from the bracket.

(2) Disconnect the engine coolant temperature sensor connector.

(b) Release the lock lever and disconnect the brake booster pump assembly connector as shown in the illustration.

Release

Disconnect

NOTICE:

Be careful not to allow any brake fluid to enter the connector.

(c) Disengage the clamp.

(d) Remove the 7 nuts and exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst) from the cylinder head sub-assembly.

(e) Remove the exhaust manifold to head gasket and EGR cooler gasket from the cylinder head sub-assembly.

*1

Exhaust Manifold To Head Gasket

*2

EGR Cooler Gasket

14. REMOVE NO. 2 EXHAUST MANIFOLD HEAT INSULATOR

(a) Remove the 4 bolts and No. 2 exhaust manifold heat insulator from the exhaust manifold (TWC: Front Catalyst).
